Finder's latest Ethereum Price Predictions Report suggests that ETH will reach $5.8k by 2025, with some experts predicting higher prices. Omnia Markets' Mitesh Shah is more bullish, predicting $7.5k by 2025. However, some experts, such as Boston Trading.co's Jeremy Britton, believe that ETH will never flip BTC. title: Former Goldman Sachs Executive Says Ethereum Is About To Outperform Bitcoin As Crypto Enters Late Spring - The Daily Hodl
summary: Former Goldman Sachs executive Raoul Pal says Ethereum (ETH) is set to outperform Bitcoin (BTC) as the crypto market enters a new "spring" phase, according to the Tom Demark Sequential indicator. Pal believes Ethereum-based exchange-traded funds (ETFs) will be the "holy grail" for asset managers, but one crypto analyst has a conflicting view, predicting that Bitcoin Dominance (BTC.D) will continue to be bullish and altcoins, including ETH, will lag behind. Ethereum is currently trading at $2,080.

title: Not everything is about ETH as Ethereum’s revenue raises eyebrows - AMBCrypto News
summary: Ethereum's revenue hit $10 billion as demand for ETH increased, with network activity and transactions also rising. However, the growth in revenue and active addresses was short-lived, with network growth and active addresses dropping later in the week. The decrease in gas fees has affected the revenue, and for Ethereum to surpass the $10 billion mark again, demand for ETH needs to increase further.

title: Investment Titan BlackRock Questions SEC, Argues Spot Bitcoin and Ethereum ETFs Not Different From Futures ETFs - The Daily Hodl
summary: BlackRock, the largest asset management firm, is challenging the SEC's denial of spot Bitcoin and Ethereum exchange-traded funds (ETFs), arguing that they are no different from futures ETFs. BlackRock believes that the SEC is misusing the Investment Company Act of 1940 by applying it to spot ETFs, and that the distinction between futures and spot ETFs is arbitrary. The firm has registered its iShares Ethereum trust in Delaware, a move similar to its registration of its Bitcoin trust. BlackRock believes that the SEC should approve spot market crypto ETFs as it has already greenlit futures ETFs.

title: Institutional and Whale Demand for Bitcoin and Ethereum Skyrockets - U.Today
summary: Institutional and whale demand for Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Polygon has surged due to renewed institutional interest. Bitcoin saw an 80% increase in $100,000+ transactions, Ethereum's large transactions soared 170%, and Polygon experienced an unprecedented 3,800% rise. This growth is attributed to the anticipation of spot Bitcoin ETFs by January 2024 and BlackRock's plans to introduce a spot Ethereum ETF. As institutional demand brings substantial capital and credibility to the crypto market, it is expected to fuel long-term growth and mainstream acceptance of cryptocurrencies.
